deck: An enemy of Cyborg
description:
Origin

A childhood friend of Vic Stone, Keiji Otani was handed the passwords for high-level STAR Labs access by his friend. Using them to hack STAR and sell their secrets, Keiji was incarcerated in a juvenile facility, where he was frequently attacked by fellow inmates, and forbidden to use computers. Finding a Game Boy, he repairs it and, by becoming proficient with it, discovers an 8-bit universe into which he is able to escape. However, he is beaten to death before he can flee. A code version of him takes the name H8-Bit and takes up residence in the 8-bit universe.

Creation

H8-Bit was created by John Semper, Jr. and Will Conrad. He made his first appearance in Cyborg #11.

Major Story Arcs

H8-Bit

H8-Bit is accidentally confronted by Cyborg in his 8-bit universe, inside a real version of the game they created as youths, Perilandria. Seizing the opportunity, he attempts to direct the perils of Perilandria against Cyborg as revenge for how Cyborg indirectly caused him to be imprisoned and then apparently forgot him. They fight, and when Cyborg attempts to escape he pursues him to Detroit. He begins to attack people in the city, claiming he is seeking revenge, but is dragged back to Perilandria by Cyborg. He reveals that he has been dead all along, and fades away when Cyborg forcibly crashes the game.

Powers and Abilities

H8-Bit is the digital ghost of an expert hacker and programmer. He has electricity-based powers of uncertain provenance or function. He is able to fire energy blasts from his hands, the effects of which are unclear; potentially he simply pixelates things. Despite being a code, he is able to survive in the real world through unknown means.

deck: The leader of the villainous group Capers, Inc. He is an enemy of Static.
description:
History

Run is the leader of a criminal trio called Capers, Inc. He along with Jump and Burn made a reputation as bank robbers in Midwest using their powers. Their next target brought them to the Mason Building in Dakota. Their heist was fold by the city's resident superhero Static.

In Other Media

Run appears along with Jump in an episode of Static Shock (Season 2 Episode 2 - "Powerplay"). In this version, he is not a leader like his comic book counterpart. He is instead a minion of a Bang Baby named Ragtag. And unlike his powers in the comics, Ragtag gave Run the power of speed, thus making him human with limited abilities (and making his moniker more meaningful). He and Jump persuade Richie Foley to join Ragtag and commit crimes to keep their powers. Eventually, Richie, as Push, refuse to be a criminal and helps Static defeat Ragtag and his minions. He was voiced by Philip Tanzini.
name: Run

deck: A member of the villainous group Capers, Inc. He is an enemy of Static.
description:
History

Jump is a member of Capers, Inc. - a trio of costumed super-villains consisting of Run, Jump, and Burn. Capers, Inc. came to Dakota to steal from the late Edwin Alva's money vault but were stopped by Static.

Jump later resurfaces and appears he has left Capers, Inc. to join Dr. Kilgore's newly formed team of supervillains consisting of The Swarm, The Botanist, Rubberband Man, and Prometheus to seek revenge Static and drain his blood. They're attempt failed when Swarm betrays the team after some persuasion from Frieda Goren by freeing Static and gets stun by Swarm along with Botanist. Was last seen being heavily guarded by the police at a local hospital to recuperate from his injuries

In Other Media

Run appears along with Run in an episode of Static Shock (Season 2 Episode 2 - "Powerplay"). In this version, he is not Caucasian like his comic book counterpart and is changed into American-American instead. He and Run are minions to a Bang Baby named Ragtag. Unlike his powers from the comics, Ragtag gave Jump the power of teleportation, thus making him human with limited abilities (and making his moniker more meaningful). He and Run persuade Richie to join Ragtag and commit crimes to keep their powers. Eventually, Richie, as Push, refuse to be a criminal and helps Static defeat Ragtag and his minions. He was voiced by Kenny Blank.
name: Jump

The Eel of Blessed Waters was created by Ed Brisson and Mike D. Perkins. He made his first appearance in Iron Fist #2.

Major Story Arcs

The Trial of the Seven Masters

The Eel fights and nearly defeats Iron Fist as the first of the champions that Liu-Shi brings against the hero. However, Iron Fist rallies and is able to defeat him.

Powers and Abilities

The Eel is very skilled in his House's style of kung fu. He is able to generate electricity, which he uses to enhance his strikes.
